ğŸ® Video Games Sales & Ratings Analysis
ğŸ“Œ Project Overview
This project performs an Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on a massive dataset of video games to uncover trends in sales, platform popularity, and the relationship between critic scores and commercial success.

ğŸ“‚ Dataset Overview
The dataset contains 64,016 records of video games with the following attributes:

Game Info: title, console (platform), genre, publisher, developer, release_date.

Performance Metrics:

critic_score: Aggregate score from critics.

total_sales(mil): Total global sales in millions.

Regional Sales (in millions):

na_sales(mil): North America.

jp_sales(mil): Japan.

pal_sales(mil): Europe/Africa (PAL region).

other_sales(mil): Other regions.

Data Cleaning:

Date Parsing: Converted release_date to datetime objects to enable time-series analysis.

Missing Values: The dataset originally contained significant missing data (e.g., ~57k missing critic scores, ~45k missing sales figures). These were handled (likely imputed or filled) to ensure statistical models and plots could run without errors, resulting in a clean dataset with 0 null values for the final analysis.

ğŸ” Key Insights & Analysis
1. ğŸ“Š Correlation Analysis
A correlation heatmap was generated to understand relationships between numerical variables. Key relationships typically explored in this domain include:

Critic Score vs. Sales: Investigating if higher critical acclaim actually leads to higher sales numbers.

Regional Correlations: Analyzing if success in North America (na_sales) correlates strongly with success in Europe (pal_sales) or Japan (jp_sales).

2. ğŸ•¹ï¸ Platform (Console) Popularity
Distribution: A count plot was generated to visualize the number of games released per console (PS3, PS4, X360, etc.).

Insight: This highlights which consoles have the largest libraries and market presence over the dataset's timeframe.

3. ğŸ“ˆ Regional Sales Trends
The dataset breaks down sales by region, allowing for comparison of market preferences:

NA vs. JP vs. PAL: Identifying which genres or consoles perform better in specific parts of the world (e.g., JRPGs in Japan vs. Shooters in North America).

ğŸ“Š Visualizations Generated
The notebook includes the following visualizations to communicate insights:

Correlation Heatmap: To visualize the strength of relationships between sales figures and scores.

Pairplot: A comprehensive grid of scatterplots to visualize pairwise relationships across all numerical variables.

Console Countplot: A bar chart showing the frequency of games across different gaming platforms.

